				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p> Regional commentators characterised the meeting as ‘difficult’. A key component of the problems faced by the region relates to the diversity of economic arrangements and situations within the Caribbean (particularly the situation of eastern Caribbean states, the situation of highly indebted countries and the partial coverage of the targeted Caribbean ‘Single Market and Economy’). It is the importance of getting to grips with these intra-regional issues which lies at the heart of the growing frustration at the difficulties in securing practical support from the EC and the Caribbean’s insistence on variable geometry within an EPA.</p>
		</div>
		
